General info - Crag Guru on Facebook

<p>Crag Guru is a window into a massive database of rock climbing routes and climber ascents. It is for rock climbers who want to know more about the climbs at a crag. Without leaving your Facebook account Crag Guru lets you:</p>

<p style="margin:2em; text-align: center;"><a class="fbButton" href="http://apps.facebook.com/cragguru/"><span>Try CragGuru on Facebook</span></a></p>

<ul>
  <li><p>Search for climbing routes in any area from thecrag.com's database (about 170,000 climbs recorded); and</p></li>
  <li><p>Ask cool questions about climb statistics derived from ascents logged by the rock climbing community (about 410,000 ascents logged).</p></li>
</ul>

<p>For example you may ask Crag Guru the following questions about climbs in any country, area or crag in the world.</p>

<ul>
  <li><p>What are the most popular climbs?</p></li>
  <li><p>What are the grade icons?</p></li>
  <li><p>What are the highest quality routes?</p></li>
  <li><p>What climbs does Crag Guru recommend for you?</p></li>
  <li><p>What are the hardest routes?</p></li>
  <li><p>What are the easiest routes?</p></li>
</ul>

<p>To get the best results, create a free account on thecrag.com, keep a record of your climbs and link it ot this service. Crag Guru will then personalize its results for you.</p>

<p>If you create an account on thecrag.com and link it to this service then Crag Guru can tailor the answers to you. If you have logged your own ascents then recommendations will be based on your ascent profile.<p>

<p>This service is brought to you by thecrag.com.</p>

<h2>About thecrag.com</h2>

<p>thecrag.com is the original site for logging climbing ascents (since 1999) and is the only site offering ascent logging based on a comprehensive index of climbs.</p>

<p>For a more complete experience you should go directly to thecrag.com.</p>


<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

<p>thecrag.com is committed to respecting the privacy of its customers. The following policy discusses how personal information received by thecrag.com will be dealt with in respect to the 'Crag Guru' application on Facebook.</p>

<p>To operate the application you must install it on your Facebook account.</p>

<p>The application uses your Facebook account identifier to operate. It is the intention of the application to link your thecrag.com account with your Facebook account.</p>

<p>Once linked, query results are personalised based on your thecrag.com account settings and ascent profile.</p>

<p>The application does not use any other personal Facebook information to deliver the service.</p>

<p>Your Facebook account identifier is is stored securily in our system. This information is not passed on to any third party unless requested by the user, required to by law or as the direct fulfilment of the offered service.</p>

<p>We may use this information to help identify you for other services offered by thecrag.com on Facebook.</p>

<p>We are planning some future enhancements which will require the application to access your list of friends. When this enhancement becomes available we will update our privacy policy to cover this scenario.</p>


<h2>Support</h2>

<p>You may contact thecrag.com support email (&#115;&#117;&#112;&#112;&#111;&#114;&#116; &#64;  thecrag.com) if you require any support for this service.</p>
